Sentencas: Porous metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells (PMS-SOFCs) demonstrate potential to dramatically reduce their costs while simultaneously enhancing the durability of SOFCs.
Titulo: Vacuum cold sprayed nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for porous metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating below 600 °C

Sentencas: However, owing to the unsatisfactory performance improvement of PMS-SOFCs at low temperatures and available fabrication processes, their commercial applications are limited.
Titulo: Vacuum cold sprayed nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for porous metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating below 600 °C

Sentencas: In this study, exceptional performance of PMS-SOFCs for electricity generation at low temperatures (400-600 degrees C) with vacuum cold sprayed (VCS) nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-delta_(LSCF) as the high-activity cathode, the plasma-sprayed Ce0.8Gd0.2O2-delta/ La0.8Sr0.2Ga0.8Mg0.2O3-delta (GDC/LSGM) bilayer as the electrolyte, and a cermet consisting of the nickel-gadolinium-doped-ceria (Ni-GDC) composite as the anode.
Titulo: Vacuum cold sprayed nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for porous metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating below 600 °C

Sentencas: By carefully controlling the spray particle size, a nanostructured LSCF cathode is obtained, and the oxygen reduction reaction (ORR) is activated.
Titulo: Vacuum cold sprayed nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for porous metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating below 600 °C

Sentencas: Consequently, the microstructurally optimized cell exhibits remarkable peak power densities of >1 W/cm(2) at 600 degrees C and >0.2 W/cm(2) at 450 degrees C. Moreover, this nanostructured cathode maintains high activity over 1000 h at 550 degrees C due to the stable microstructure, strontium (Sr) surface segregation, and the exceptional stability of PMS-SOFCs.
Titulo: Vacuum cold sprayed nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for porous metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating below 600 °C

Sentencas: Our results demonstrate a simple route to dramatically improve the performance and stability of PMS-SOFCs operating at low temperatures by using a nanoscale cathode for activity toward the ORR.
Titulo: Vacuum cold sprayed nanostructured La0.6Sr0.4Co0.2Fe0.8O3-δ as a high-performance cathode for porous metal-supported solid oxide fuel cells operating below 600 °C
